
=Bio=

"I'm the President of New York Chapter of Internet Society (ISOC-NY), a nonprofit that works for open development of technology, Internet freedom and access for all. We're a Chapter of the global Internet Society (ISOC) founded by Vint Cerf, "the father of the Internet".

I'm also CEO of Zoetic Networks LLC, which develops open technologies for social good that are outside of the core ISOC mission. They include blockchain and smart contracts, security for IoT, medical implants and prostheses, and wireless mesh networks for areas with poor connectivity. Currently developing a fund using Ethereum to support these projects."


